##Confidence Intervals for UCM

*Confidence Interval for 2nd Year Retention Rate

# bootstrap distribution
UCM_BS2 <- UCM_Regression %>%
  specify(response = `2nd Year Retention Rate`) %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "bootstrap") %>%
  calculate(stat = "mean")
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values.
UCM_BS2 %>%
  get_confidence_interval(level = 0.95, type = "percentile")
## # A tibble: 1  2
##   lower_ci upper_ci
##      <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1    0.818    0.841
UCM_BS2_1 <- UCM_BS2 %>%
  get_ci(point_estimate = mean(UCM_BS2$stat),
         level = 0.95, type = "se")

visualize(UCM_BS2) +
  shade_ci(endpoints = UCM_BS2_1, color = "#DAA900", fill = "#002856")
